               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Independent advocacy service for adults primarily in order to meet the requirement for service provision under the:</P>
                  <P>— Adults with Incapacity (Scotland) Act 2000.</P>
                  <P>— Mental Health (Care and Treatment) (Scotland) Act 2003.</P>
                  <P>— Adult Support and Protection (Scotland) Act 2007.</P>
                  <P>— And possibly the Carers (Scotland) Act 2016.</P>
                  <P>In exceptional circumstances health or social care staff may make a referral to the service where the adult is not subject to any of the above legislation.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
